casebody.data:
CITY OF LINDEN, PROSECUTOR, v. BOARD OF PUBLIC UTILITY COMMISSIONERS, RESPONDENT — ELIZABETHTOWN WATER COMPANY, CONSOLIDATED, INTERVENING. Decided June 22, 1925.

Before Justices Trexchaed and Lloyd.

Eor the application, Whittemore & McLean. Eor the respondent, Collins & Corbin. Per Curiam.

Our examination of the application for the writ of certiorari in this case, together with the affidavits and arguments concerning the same, leads us to the conclusion that the writ should be denied, and it is denied accordingly.
